        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3904746033" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer147839322894702365">I am glad that I finally read this book!<br/><br/>The first time I read about Saint Thérèse of the Child Jesus was during my confirmation, as I had chosen her as my confirmation saint. At that time, while I knew that she was one of the most loved Catholic saints in the world, I did not try to learn more about her life.<br/><br/>It was only last year after I had the good fortune of receiving her precious relics from the Carmel nuns in Lisieux, that I became more interested to read more about her life and sufferings.</span>
  <span id="freeText147839322894702365" style="display:none">I am glad that I finally read this book!<br /><br />The first time I read about Saint Thérèse of the Child Jesus was during my confirmation, as I had chosen her as my confirmation saint. At that time, while I knew that she was one of the most loved Catholic saints in the world, I did not try to learn more about her life.<br /><br />It was only last year after I had the good fortune of receiving her precious relics from the Carmel nuns in Lisieux, that I became more interested to read more about her life and sufferings. <br /><br />After reading this book, I think I am amazed at her simplicity and devotion. Her thoughts and approach to the various incidents are quite inspiring to read. <br /><br />Loved this autobiography!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="147839322894702365" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
