<div id="review_2842364932" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2842364932" />
    <a title="Mariangel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42781931-mariangel"><img alt="Mariangel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524160143p2/42781931.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2842364932?book_show_action=true">Aug 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mariangel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mariangel" href="/user/show/42781931-mariangel">Mariangel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 226624972X" href="/book/show/26171151-histoire-d-une-ame">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2842364932" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10353079158929380894">This is my second reading of St. Therese&apos;s book (the first in English, now in French). This edition included, in addition to her autobiography, some of her poems and prayers, and a list of miracles and favors obtained by her intercession, which were not in the English edition.<br/><br/>What a wonderful soul, and how clearly she explains her insights about God&apos;s love and mercy, supporting them with quotes from the Bible and from the poems of St. John of the Cross. This is a book worth rereading many times.</span>
  <span id="freeText10353079158929380894" style="display:none">This is my second reading of St. Therese's book (the first in English, now in French). This edition included, in addition to her autobiography, some of her poems and prayers, and a list of miracles and favors obtained by her intercession, which were not in the English edition.<br /><br />What a wonderful soul, and how clearly she explains her insights about God's love and mercy, supporting them with quotes from the Bible and from the poems of St. John of the Cross. This is a book worth rereading many times.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10353079158929380894" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


